com.ibm.team.build.common.model

Interface IBuildResult

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IBuildItem, IBuildItemHandle, IBuildResultHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle

    public interface IBuildResult
extends IBuildResultHandle, IAuditable, IBuildItem
    The result of a build. A build result is typically created at the start of a build and used as a place to record status, logs, and other contributions as the build executes.
    Since:
    0.5

      • setStatus

        void setStatus(BuildStatus status)
        Set the build status. Status cannot be set to a less severe status than its current value. For example, if the status is currently BuildStatus.ERROR, it cannot be set to BuildStatus.OK. When a result is created, its status is initialized to BuildStatus.OK. Throughout a build, as contributions are added to a result, the result's status may be updated to a more severe status, but not a less severe status.
        Parameters:
        status - The build result status.
